Absolutely delicious and a favorite of friends and family. Made several times now, always adhering to the recipe (no reason to deviate). I do recommend the best plain yogurt you can find: Greek (best)or CanadianAmerican yogurts redefine "bland." Serve with any green vegetable (roasted brussel sprouts are a good accompaniment; so are baby limas), as well as a starch if desired: Italian-style pan-fried potatoes or french fries are good with this.

Rating: 4
Excellent. A great new way to do pork tenderloin. Can imagine with other sauces (creamy mustard?) as well, but we loved the caper sauce. I used panko for the crumbs. I think using enough oil is what made it easy to cook and so crispy. Usually I would try to just cook something like this in minimum of oil, but I went with the 1/4 inch, and it was definitely worth it. I also served with a mango salsa, as mentioned below. Great combo on top of arugula. I also cut them a little bit thicker, just over 1 1/2", because they squish down after you've cut them. The thickness is what keeps the centers from being overcooked, while the outside gets brown and crunchy. I don't write reviews very often, so when I do, it's for a real keeper.

